    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review Government use of BMI, and definitions for obesity and overweight",
        "additional_details": "The Government should base policy on an improved system that uses medical advances to assess if a person is a healthy weight.\r\n \r\nThere are various factors to take into consideration to determine a person's healthy weight. I believe the BMI system is flawed and obsolete.\r\n \r\nThe Government should not encourage people to determine their own healthy weight based on just their height and weight, or use this measure to inform policy.",
        "background": "This scale does not take into consideration muscle mass, bone density or water retention and its use can cause or exacerbate eating disorders.",
